The article is a statement issued by Melania and Donald Trump on December 12, 2017, in which they extend their wishes to Jewish families celebrating Hanukkah. They highlight the significance of the holiday, which commemorates the miracles of the past and the promises of the future. The statement also recounts the historical context of Hanukkah, when practicing Judaism was punishable by death. It mentions the small band of Jewish patriots who reclaimed their Jewish identity by defeating a powerful army and rededicating their holy temple. The article emphasizes the miracle of the oil that lasted for eight days, even though there was only enough for one night. Melania and Donald Trump express their support for the Jewish people and the State of Israel, acknowledging their resilience and miraculous history. The statement concludes by wishing everyone observing the holiday a wonderful celebration.